data.enText: used to say that you think that sth is probably true
Presumably this is where the accident happened.

data.chText: 想必您是要买这辆汽车了？
data.enText: You'll be taking the car, presumably?

data.chText: 我的精神集中不起来，大概是太累了吧。
data.enText: I couldn't concentrate, presumably because I was so tired.

simple_means.memory_skill: presume 假设 + ably 可…地，…地 → 据推测；大概

value.def: If you say that something is presumably the case, you mean that you think it is very likely to be the case, although you are not certain.

example.ex: Presumably the front door was locked when you came down this morning?...
example.tran: 早上你下楼的时候，前门大概是锁上的吧？

example.ex: The spear is presumably the murder weapon...
example.tran: 这支鱼叉可能就是凶器。

example.ex: He had gone to the reception desk, presumably to check out.
example.tran: 他已经去前台了，可能是要办理退房手续。

gramarinfo.label: ADV with cl/group, ADV before v

value.tran: 大概；很可能；也许；据推测

partsOfSpeech.dec: dishonour 使丢脸 + ably 可…地，…地 → 不名誉地；可耻地
equit〔= equi公平〕+ ably 可…地，…地 → 公平地 → 公正地
favour 赞成；有利于 + ably 可…地，…地 → 赞成地；顺利地
note 注意 + ably 可…地，…地 → 明显地
presume 假设 + ably 可…地，…地 → 据推测；大概
reason 推理 + ably 可…地，…地 → 适度地；相当地
suit 合适 + ably 可…地，…地 → 恰当地
